{"parse":{"title":"Stubble burning","pageid":40341018,"revid":852221664,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Stubble_burning_in_North_Essex_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1448777.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a6/Stubble_burning_in_North_Essex_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1448777.jpg/220px-Stubble_burning_in_North_Essex_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1448777.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"142\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a6/Stubble_burning_in_North_Essex_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1448777.jpg/330px-Stubble_burning_in_North_Essex_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1448777.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a6/Stubble_burning_in_North_Essex_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1448777.jpg/440px-Stubble_burning_in_North_Essex_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1448777.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"640\" data-file-height=\"413\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Stubble_burning_in_North_Essex_-_geograph.org.uk_-_1448777.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Stubble burning in Essex, England in 1986</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Stubble burning</b> is the deliberate setting fire of the straw <a href=\"/wiki/Crop_residue\" title=\"Crop residue\">stubble</a> that remains after wheat and other grains have been harvested. The practice was widespread until the 1990s, when governments increasingly restricted its use.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Effects\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Effects</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Attitudes_to_stubble_burning\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Attitudes to stubble burning</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Stubble_burning_in_India\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Stubble burning in India</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Effects\">Effects</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Stubble_burning&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Effects\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:NP_India_burning_48_(6315309342).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/90/NP_India_burning_48_%286315309342%29.jpg/220px-NP_India_burning_48_%286315309342%29.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"146\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/90/NP_India_burning_48_%286315309342%29.jpg/330px-NP_India_burning_48_%286315309342%29.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/90/NP_India_burning_48_%286315309342%29.jpg/440px-NP_India_burning_48_%286315309342%29.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1280\" data-file-height=\"850\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:NP_India_burning_48_(6315309342).jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Burning of rice residues after harvest, to quickly prepare the land for wheat planting, around <a href=\"/wiki/Sangrur\" title=\"Sangrur\">Sangrur</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Punjab,_India\" title=\"Punjab, India\">Punjab, India</a>.</div></div></div>\n<p>The burning of stubble, contrasted with alternatives such as ploughing the stubble back into the ground has a number of consequences and effects on the environment<sup id=\"cite_ref-vicgovau_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-vicgovau-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Stubble burning:\n</p>\n<ul><li>Quickly clears the field and is cheap.</li>\n<li>Kills weeds, including those resistant to herbicide.</li>\n<li>Kills slugs and other pests.</li>\n<li>Can reduce nitrogen tie-up</li></ul>\n<p>However, it has a number of harmful effects on the environment:\n</p>\n<ul><li>Loss of nutrients.</li>\n<li>Pollution from smoke.</li>\n<li>Damage to electrical and electronic equipment from floating threads of conducting waste.</li>\n<li>Risk of fires spreading out of control<sup id=\"cite_ref-mailtimes_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-mailtimes-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<p>There is a perception that stubble burning contributes to atmospheric CO<sub>2</sub>. However carbon dioxide releases are only slightly greater than those from natural decomposition<sup id=\"cite_ref-vicgovau_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-vicgovau-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Attitudes_to_stubble_burning\">Attitudes to stubble burning</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Stubble_burning&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Attitudes to stubble burning\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Stubble burning has been effectively prohibited since 1993 in England and Wales.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> A perceived increase in <a href=\"/wiki/Alopecurus_myosuroides\" title=\"Alopecurus myosuroides\">blackgrass</a>, and particularly herbicide resistant blackgrass, has led to a campaign by some arable farmers for its return.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>In Australia stubble burning is \"not the preferred option for the majority of farmers\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-vicgovau_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-vicgovau-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> but is permitted and recommended in some circumstances. Farmers are advised to rake and burn windrows, and leave a fire break of 3 metres around any burn off.<sup id=\"cite_ref-mailtimes_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-mailtimes-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>In the United States, fires are fairly common in mid-western states. Many of the fires in the video are started deliberately.</li></ul>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><div id=\"mwe_player_0\" class=\"PopUpMediaTransform\" style=\"width:220px;\" videopayload=\"&lt;div class=&quot;mediaContainer&quot; style=&quot;width:854px&quot;&gt;&lt;video id=&quot;mwe_player_1&quot; poster=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/30/Fires_observed_in_the_United_States_From_July_2002_through_July_2011.ogv/854px--Fires_observed_in_the_United_States_From_July_2002_through_July_2011.ogv.jpg&quot; controls=&quot;&quot; preload=&quot;none&quot; autoplay=&quot;&quot; style=&quot;width:854px;height:480px&quot; class=&quot;kskin&quot; data-durationhint=&quot;72.539138321995&quot; data-startoffset=&quot;0&quot; data-mwtitle=&quot;Fires_observed_in_the_United_States_From_July_2002_through_July_2011.ogv&quot; data-mwprovider=&quot;wikimediacommons&quot;&gt;&lt;source src=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/transcoded/3/30/Fires_observed_in_the_United_States_From_July_2002_through_July_2011.ogv/Fires_observed_in_the_United_States_From_July_2002_through_July_2011.ogv.480p.webm&quot; type=&quot;video/webm; codecs=&amp;